name: Dictionary.Index
desc: The position of a key-value pair in a dictionary.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of this value by feeding them into the given hasher.

items.name: static func ... (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> PartialRangeFrom<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

items.name: static func ... (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> PartialRangeThrough<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

items.name: static func ... (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> ClosedRange<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

items.name: static func < (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

items.name: static func <= (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

items.name: static func == (Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool
